A woman and her dog were killed in Germany when both were struck by a train as she tried to rescue the pet that had wandered onto the tracks, Police said on Thursday. The 53-year-old had desperately hurried after her dog as it ran into the path of the oncoming train in the Bavarian town of Garmisch-Partenkirchen on Wednesday. The accident shut down a section of railway for three hours. (dpa/NAN) UNITED STATES: Deaths as rail carriages fall on US motorway Dog to be killed after autopsy shows he killed owners Police arrest dog, 2 persons over robbery